Alan Ford is an English actor . He was born on March 14 , 1945 in London , and trained at East 15 Acting School . He is perhaps best known today for his roles in the Guy Ritchie crime capers Lock , Stock and Two Smoking Barrels and Snatch and guest starring in The Bill.He also appeared in Exorcist : The Beginning and , much earlier , as ' Roosta ' in the original radio version of The Hitchhiker 's Guide to the Galaxy . Ford also had a brief role in the film , An American Werewolf in London , he plays the taxi driver who says the line ; " It puts you in mind of the days of the old demon barber of Fleet Street , does n't it ? " , in response to the recent wave of murders around London . He has also proved himself a superb comic actor , albeit one playing the familiar ' East End Thug ' role , in the Armando Iannucci productions Knowing Me , Knowing You . . . with Alan Partridge playing a boxing promoter called Terry Norton and The Armando Iannucci Shows . Despite the stereotyping of his character , his timing and presence within these shows were simultaneously hilarious and terrifying . He has also portrayed a similar role in radio adverts for Virgin Media . He is famed for his very East London cockney accent which adds to his ' mobster ' roles . 